 "description": "Highly intelligent monsters of magical nature. Spells fail against them often: base 75% resistance against an 11th-level caster, shifting 5% per level (a 12th-level Magic-User faces 70%). They cannot be subdued, though a strong Chaotic character may enlist one — and may find the Balrog moves to take command instead, for Chaotic creatures obey a Balrog before any human save an Evil High Priest. Against fantastic opponents a Balrog strikes twice each turn: a +1 magical sword, and — if it immolates, on 7+ with 2d6 checked each melee turn — its whip, which on a hit drags the victim against the flaming body for two dice of damage.",
